Analysis: Average Batavia Public School District 101 teacher compensation is $98,639

Schools

By LGIS News Service | Dec 10, 2018


AddThis Sharing Sidebar
Share to Facebook
, Number of shares
Share to TwitterShare to Reddit
, Number of shares
More AddThis Share options
, Number of shares
Hide
Show

The average teacher at Batavia Public School District 101 received $98,639 in total compensation during the 2015-2016 school year for working nine months, according to an analysis of Illinois State Board of Education (ISBE) and Teachers Retirement System (TRS) records by the Kane County Reporter.

The analysis covers 635 district employees who received a collective $62.6 million in 2015-2016.

The total compensation number was calculated by combining base salary for nine months, cost of benefits (at 30 percent), paid sick days and taxpayer-funded pension contributions for each employee.

The pension contribution was 37 percent of each employee's base salary in 2016, according to TRS.

Public school employees pay into the state pension system approximately 3 percent of what they stand to collect in retirement, or $30,000 for each $1 million received. Taxpayers make up the difference.

Of the employee pay packages analyzed, 333 of the 635 (52 percent) received more than $100,000; and 12 earned more than $200,000, including top-compensated District Superintendent Lisa Hichens ($331,231) and one teacher.
